SIMPLE: knee-deep
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Knee-deep
<hw>Knee"-deep`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rising
to the knees; knee-high; <as>as, water or snow
<ex>knee-deep</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Grass <qex>knee-deep</qex> within a month.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sunk to the knees; <as>as, men <ex>knee-deep</ex> in
water</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where <qex>knee-deep</qex> the trees were standing.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knee-high</ent>⟦br⟧
